cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 

- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the use of social media platforms (Facebook and Twitter) in political communication during an election campaign. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper uses a Bayesian language model to identify political topics in social media messages. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper discusses the mediation of political communication on social media and the impact of sociotechnical environments. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is relevant as the paper analyzes the behavior of politicians and their audiences on social media platforms. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve the analysis of multimedia content (e.g. images, videos) posted by politicians on social media.
